From da7a6e901324d786257059635329f6cecfede6e1 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: melnoff <melnoff360@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 25 Apr 2026 16:43:22 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] feat(net): VLESS subscription path through sing-box urltest
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Adds the runtime plumbing for subscription-mode VLESS proxies on top
of patch 09's parser/fetcher:

  * bridge.go: extracts the inbound + log + route wrapper into a
    private startBoxWithOutbounds() helper, then exposes
    SingboxStartSubscription() — accepts a JSON outbounds array
    (built by BuildSingboxSubscriptionOutboundsJson, includes a
    "proxy"-tagged urltest selector) and launches the same
    Socks5-fronted sidecar. SingboxStart() is rewired to share the
    helper.
  * VlessBridge: adds ensureRunningSubscription(key, servers) and
    stopSubscription(key) on a separate _runningSubscriptions map
    keyed by subscription URL. Loads the new SingboxStartSubscription
    export and refuses to operate if it is missing. shutdownAll()
    stops both maps. Common id->Running collection lifted into
    startAndCollect().
  * vless_bridge.h gains a forward include of vless_parser.h for
    the new VlessParams parameter type.

End-to-end this means: one subscription URL → one sing-box sidecar
that internally urltests across all subscription servers and exposes
a single stable local Socks5 to tdesktop. UI wiring lands in patch 11.
